node.text:
How to Slice and DIce and Avocado. Follow these steps👇🏻
- Cut an avocado in half along the seed
- Separate the two sides of the avocado
- For the diced version, slice the inside part of the avocado lengthwise, and then cut it perpendicular to create the dice
- Use a spoon to scoop out the flesh
- For the slices, do the exact same thing except don't cut it the second time
- Scoop out the inside like you would for the diced avocado!

Deep Fried Cheese Curds. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Combine 1 cup of all purpose flour with 2 tablespoons of baking powder, and 1 tablespoon of onion salt
- In another bowl, combine 3 eggs with 1 cup of cold soda water
- Combine the wet ingredients with the dry ingredients until you get a thin pancake batter consistency
- In another bowl add 2 cups of panko breadcrumbs
- Add a few cheese curds to a wooden skewer 
- Dip the cheese curds in the wet batter
- Bring them over to the bowl of panko bread crumbs and toss them until they are fully coated
- Fry the cheese coated cheese curds in 375 degree F cooking oil for 2 minutes or Air Fry them at 400 for 7-8 minutes

Sausage Stuffed Breakfast Doughnuts. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Add 1 pound of breakfast sausage to a medium high frying pan
- Cook the sausage for 5-7 minutes until it becomes brown and crispy and transfer it to a bowl
- To the bowl of sausage, add 1 cup of room temperature cream cheese and 1 cup of mozzarella cheese, and 2 tablespoons of chopped parsley
- Slice a large white onion in half making sure to keep the rounds in place and separate the onion layers
- Add some of the sausage and cheese mixture to the onion and using your finger, create a hole.
- Place them in the fridge or freezer for 20 minutes
- For the batter, combine 2 cups of all purpose flour, 2 tablespoons of baking powder, a pinch of salt, 2 eggs and 1 1/2 cups of cold club soda
- Take the onion out of the fridge or freezer and stick a wooden skewer through it to help dunk it in the batter
- Dunk it in the batter making sure to cover the entire thing, and fry it in 375 degrees F cooking oil for roughly 3 minutes
- Add a slice of cheese and a fried egg, garnish with some chopped chives
- #neverskipeggday

Chocolate Covered Strawberry Pancake Bites. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Add 1 cup of dark chocolate chips to a microwave safe bowl
- Place them in the microwave for 30 seconds and stir. Repeat this a few more times until all the chocolate chips are melted
- Use a straw to poke a strawberry from the bottom to the top in order to remove the green leafy stem and the flavorless white center
- Slice the strawberries into smaller pieces and coat them in the melted chocolate
- Place the chocolate covered strawberries on a parchment paper lined baking tray and place them in the fridge or freezer for 20 minutes so the chocolate can harder
- In the meantime make your favorite pancake batter
- An easy way to elevate your pancake batter is adding some cinnamon
- Once the chocolate has hardened, take them out of the fridge or freezer and coat them in the pancake batter
- Fry each bite for a few minutes on one side, just until it starts to bubble
- Flip the pancake bites and cook for a few more minutes
- Dip them in maple syrup or enjoy them as is!
